  &lt;p id="opCbaW"&gt;If you had any remaining hopes, despite &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/3/24191966/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-flip-6-spec-leak"&gt;leak&lt;/a&gt; upon &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/28/24188017/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-fold-6-leak-renders-colors-unpacked"&gt;leak&lt;/a&gt;, that Samsung’s foldables would get a major update this year, then I hate to be the bearer of bad news. They’re a little more durable, a little lighter, and come with a handful of tiny upgrades. Even so, both models &lt;a href="https://howl.me/cmDKOyRtZR8"&gt;got a boost&lt;/a&gt; of a certain kind: higher prices, with the Galaxy Z Fold 6 now starting at $1,899 and the Z Flip 6 at $1,099. &lt;/p&gt;
